{"word":"ἀμήν","slug":"ἀμήν","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀμήν</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ Heb.\">Heb.</a>] <b><i>amen,</i></b> strong affirmation in worshipful statement = <i>so let it be</i> <b><a href='B:520 1:25'>Ro 1:25</a>; <a href='B:530 14:16'>1 Cor 14:16</a>; <a href='B:540 1:20'>2 Cor 1:20</a>; <a href='B:550 1:5'>Gal 1:5</a>; <a href='B:550 6:18'>6:18</a>; <a href='B:610 1:17'>1 Ti 1:17</a>; <a href='B:670 4:11'>1 Pt 4:11</a>.</b> Frequently used by Jesus in the formula <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀμήν\">ἀμήν</a></el> + <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:λέγω\">λέγω</a></el> <b><a href='B:470 5:18'>Mt 5:18</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a>; often with doubled <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀμήν\">ἀμήν</a></el> in J. In <b><a href='B:730 3:14'>Rv 3:14</a></b> Jesus is termed the ultimate affirmation: <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ὁ\">ὁ</a> <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἀμήν\">ἀμήν</a></el>. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἄμετρος\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀμήτωρ\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}